article.headline: Brown 87, Quinnipiac 78
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Tucker Halpern had 26 points and 12 rebounds and Peter Sullivan scored 22 points as Brown defeated Quinnipiac 87-78 on Monday in a nonconference game. Halpern scored five points during a 15-1 second-half run by the Bears (7-8) that turned a 54-51 deficit into a 66-55 lead with 7:29 remaining. Brown shot 57.1 percent (16 of 28) in the second half and led by as many as 16 points, 82-66, after a first half in which neither team led by more than four. The Bobcats (12-5) came in leading the nation in rebounds per game with 43.8 but were outrebounded 35-33 by the Bears. Brown also had an edge at the free-throw line, making 26 of 32 -- including 12 of 12 by Sullivan -- to Quinnipiac's 17 of 24. Garrett Leffelman added 16 points for Brown and Sean McGonagill had eight assists. James Johnson led Quinnipiac with 19 points, Deontay Twyman had 14 and Jamee Jackson 13.
